<subSubSection pageNumber="413" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="413">
Current name: 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Cass" authorityName="Cass" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Glebionis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coronaria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageNumber="413">Glebionis coronaria</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(L.) Cass
</taxonomicName>
, ex Spach (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageNumber="413" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="413">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">
Note: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coronarium">Chrysanthemum coronarium</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
had long been treated as the 
<typeStatus>generitype</typeStatus>
until Trehane (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">Taxon</emphasis>
44: 439. 1995) proposed the conservation of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">Chrysanthemum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Burseraceae" genus="Canarium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">C. indicum</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
as the conserved type, in order to restrict the generic name to the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="floristsâ€™">florists'</normalizedToken>
chrysanthemum. The proposal was successful, resulting in 
<taxonomicName authority="Cass" authorityName="Cass" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Glebionis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">Glebionis</emphasis>
Cass
</taxonomicName>
, becoming the correct generic name for 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Hill" authorityYear="1762" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cyanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">C. segetum</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coronarium">C. coronarium</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageNumber="413" type="multiple">
<paragraph pageNumber="413">
The earliest typification of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coronarium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">C. coronarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published by Dillon (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">Fieldiana, Bot.</emphasis>
, n.s., 7: 5. 1981), who designated 1012.25 (LINN) as the type. Unfortunately, this specimen is identifiable as 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Fourr." authorityName="Fourr." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Glebionis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">Glebionis segetum</emphasis>
(L.) Fourr.
</taxonomicName>
(syn. 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">C. segetum</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
). Turland (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">Taxon</emphasis>
53: 1072. 2004) successfully proposed the conservation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coronarium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="413">C. coronarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a conserved type.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
